Diagnostics Review:

The model is not adequate because: 1. The Residuals vs Fitted plot are not randomly scattered around zero. 2.The residuals are not following a normal distribution. The extreme values in the Q-Q plot are not lying on the straight line, although improved when compared to model_1. 3. The Scale-Location plot shows that the residual variation is not occurring on a fixed band above the x-axis. The scatter shows a funnel shaped distribution, which indicates heteroskedasticity although improved when compared to model_1.

Model Interpretation:

  1. The selected predictors (median_income and ocean_proximity) explain 55.29% of the median_house_value variance. This is a mild improvement when compared to model_1.
  2. For every unit increase in the median_income, the median_house_value increases by 35,118.
  3. The median_house_value changes depending on the house location. If a house is on an island, the price increases by 200,480.2 if the median_income predictor remains the same.
